This is for the steps to build your containarized version of your Microservice go project.
1. Add the Dockerfile - Note naming is important with no ext. 
2. Modify go.mod to include your dependency 
3. Generate your go.sum  -- 
4. Build your docker image  --  docker build -t product-catalog . 2>&1 | Tee-Object -File "docker_build.log"
5. Start a container from the created image, and you should be able to access your Go application at http://localhost:8081 in your web browser or Postman. -- docker run -p 8081:8081 product-catalog

docker run -d -p 8081:8081 --name book-store --restart always product-catalog-solid
docker run -d -p 8081:8081 --name book-store product-catalog-solid

docker inspect book-store | Select-String '"Ports"'







